    },
    {
      "id": "877f0222_963cedf6",
      "file_path": "gui-editors/gui-editor-apex/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/gui/editors/apex/rest/handling/plugin/upload/PolicyUploadHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "Correct, you would use Spring config to set listen address and port:\n```\nserver.address=<your_ip>\nserver.port=<your_port>\napex-editor.upload-url=<upload_url>\napex-editor.upload-userid=<upload_userid>\n```\nSpring Boot uses 0.0.0.0:8080 as defaults, so you will need to supply your own properties file (or command line args or environment vars) to set these.\n\nSide note: I have deliberately *not* included a default application.properties file in the JAR. As per POLICY-3638, Apex Editor will be included alongside other GUIs in a single JAR. I wanted to avoid any issues from having multiple properties files on the classpath.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2022-02-22 13:39:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5769b870_0413b75f",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
